  "briefing": {
    "description": "A 45-minute multi-role sortie for two F-16Cs out of Batumi. The package includes aerial refuelling over the Black Sea, a BVR/WVR intercept of a 2-ship Su-27 CAP, and a pre-planned JDAM strike on a Russian forward command post complex near the Georgian-Russian border. Tanker Texaco (KC-135) holds a racetrack at FL220 over the Black Sea. Magic AWACS (E-3A) provides picture and will call the Su-27 bandits as a pop-up threat at the 15-minute mark.",
    "blue_task": "1. Cold-start at Batumi. Taxi and depart NW over Black Sea. 2. Rendezvous with Texaco on the AAR track at FL220, take on fuel (6 min contact). 3. Push NE after post-contact. Check in with Magic on 251.0 AM. 4. At the IP (WP5), Magic will vector you onto 2x Su-27 bandits — Iron 1-1/1-2 holding a CAP orbit. Engage BVR with AIM-9X; close if necessary. 5. After the merge, continue NE to the JDAM release point at FL220. Pre-planned targets are the Forward Command Post (BMP-2 cluster) and accompanying armour. Release GBU-38s from medium altitude; two bombs per designated aim point. 6. Egress south. Descend on descent fix and RTB Batumi. Total planned sortie: ~45 min wheels-up to touchdown.",
    "red_task": "Iron 1-1/1-2 (Su-27) hold CAP orbit N of the command post, ready to intercept any blue aircraft pushing through the FLOT. Surface-to-air assets (SA-15 Tor, ZSU-23-4) are active at the command post perimeter. EWR provides early warning to Russian GCI."
  },
