  "agent_notes": "Black Sea Hammer is a full-spectrum multi-role sortie designed to flow naturally over ~45 minutes. Phase sequence: cold-start Batumi (6 min), climb and transit NW over the Black Sea (5 min), AAR with Texaco at FL220 (6 min on the boom), push NE with Magic picture (5 min), BVR/WVR intercept of 2x Su-27 CAP (5 min), JDAM strike on the command post from FL220 medium altitude (5 min), and egress/RTB (13 min). Threat environment is medium: the Su-27s are the primary A-A threat (R-27R BVR + R-73 WVR); the SA-15 and ZSU-23-4 at the target mandate medium-altitude release. The GBU-38 STRIKE preset (4x JDAM, 2x AIM-9X) covers both the A-A fight (Sidewinder self-defence) and the ground strike. Viper slots are set to Client skill for player use. Red CAP spawns airborne on a racetrak orbit for immediate readiness."
